                            <comment id="13564930" author="jmhsieh" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 01:00:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I always considered these applications simple wrappers around the hbase-specific mr input and output formats or bulk load apis.  If you are expecting users to write customer mappers, then isn&apos;t having those formats sufficient?  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do like the idea of unifying the -D options so that all are more similar, and could see those pieces being unified better.  Is that the scope or only part of the scope you are considering?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13565044" author="jmhsieh" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 03:34:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, Snapshot Export &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6802&quot; title=&quot;Export Snapshot&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6802&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6802&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; would be in this category as well. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13566671" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2013 17:30:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s exactly my point: those existing applications are just simple examples over the input and output formats. They&apos;re not fully-features data movement applications. HBase is shaping up to be a world-class database, it should ship world-class tool to help users and administrators manage their &quot;planet-sized data&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, I believe snapshot management falls into the domain of this/these tools as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13566686" author="jmhsieh" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2013 17:53:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So are you proposing to add new framework and more code and for importing so that this can be &quot;world-class&quot;?  Help me understand what is in scope and out and maybe provide some examples or a comparison.  Is this basically just a new command line program that lets you pick arbitrary input/output format combinations?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601363" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 17:07:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing as invalid because this is pretty vague. If you&apos;re interested, see related mapreduce improvements in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8084&quot; title=&quot;Sundry mapreduce improvements&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8084&quot;&gt;HBASE-8084&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
